headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 35 points, Tyus Jones added 18 and the Memphis Grizzlies broke open a close game in the fourth quarter to beat the Sacramento Kings 118-108 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Jones lead Grizzlies to 118-108 victory over Kings

headlines.description: — Rui Hachimura had 26 points, Kristaps Porzingis scored 22 and the Washington Wizards defeated the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks 118-95 on Sunday night for their season-best fifth consecutive victory.

headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has triple-double, Nuggets top Celtics after rim delay
